colonial oven
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a long narrow iron box in the form of an oven with a door, bricked into a hearth with room for the fire on top (for boiling and stewing with pots) and under the bottom (for baking).
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
