Date: 0/0/1962
Source: Waikaka Saga
Author: EVANS
Vol / Page: 221
Edition:
Quote: Board houses replaced slab whares. ... the colonial oven entered in all its glory. The colonial oven was an elongated iron box afair, bricked into place, with provision for a fire underneath it. On top was the main cooking fire, and kettles and pots rested on iron bars above the flames or were suspended on chains.
